               <msContents>
                  <summary>
                     This 14th-century copy of the <title>Mas̲navī-i Ma‘navī</title> (Spiritual Couplets) by Jalāl al-Dīn Rūmī
                     (1207–1273) contains all six books but lacks an opening preface. Completed by a scribe named <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" role="scr">Maḥmūd ibn Mubārak</persName> in <date cert="high" calendar="Hijri_qamari" when="1357-01-02">9 Muḥarram 758 AH (2 January 1357 CE)</date>, about 85 years after the author completed it. Therefore, it not only constitutes the earliest copy of the work held in the Rylands, but it is also one of the oldest held in Britain.</summary>
                  
