                  <accMat>A letter dated 4 December
                     1975 accompanies the volume, written by David Brady (Middle Eastern Librarian in the University of Manchester
                     from the late 1960s to the 1980s) to Glenys Matheson (Keeper of
                     Manuscripts in the John Rylands Library until the 1980s):<lb/>
                     <q xml:lang="en">Dear Miss Matheson, I am sending to you a Persian manuscript
                        which has been kept in the Cataloguing Room here at least as long as
                        I have been here. I think that it is time that it joined the Persian manuscripts
                        collection at Deansgate. The appended card contains some information
                        about the manuscript, which I managed to discover a few years
                        ago. Best wishes, David Brady</q>.</accMat>               
